

Flask URL Shortener

A simple URL shortener web application built with Flask.

Table of Contents
Overview
Features
Setup
Usage
Dependencies

Overview
This Flask application allows users to shorten long URLs into shorter, more manageable ones. It provides a simple web interface where users can enter a URL, and the application generates a unique short URL for them to use.

Features
Shorten long URLs into shorter, more manageable ones.
Generates unique short URLs to avoid collisions.
Stores URL mappings in a SQLite database.

Setup
    To set up and run the application locally, follow these steps:

    Clone this repository to your local machine:

        git clone https://github.com/your-username/url-shortener.git

    Navigate to the project directory:

        cd url-shortener

        Install the dependencies:

        pip install -r requirements.txt

    Create the SQLite database:

        python create_db.py

Usage
    To run the application, execute the following command in your terminal:

        python app.py

    Once the server is running, open your web browser and navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000/. You can now start shortening URLs!

Dependencies
    The following dependencies are required to run the application:

        Flask
        SQLite3 (included in Python standard library)

